Got it â€” letâ€™s walk through the Power Query approach so you can go from your raw risk events/actions table to a â€œ% fully remediated per monthâ€ view without manual COUNTIFS.

â¸»

Step 1 â€“ Load Data into Power Query
	1.	Select your table in Excel â†’ Data tab â†’ Get & Transform â†’ From Table/Range.
	2.	Make sure your table has headers (Risk Event ID, Action Due Date, Action Closed Date, etc.).

â¸»

Step 2 â€“ Add a â€œClosed On Timeâ€ Flag
	1.	In Power Query, Add Column â†’ Custom Column:

if [Action Closed Date] <= [Action Due Date] then 1 else 0

Name this column Closed_On_Time.

â¸»

Step 3 â€“ Create â€œMonth Dueâ€ Column
	1.	Add Column â†’ Date â†’ Month â†’ Start of Month on [Action Due Date].
This creates a column you can use for monthly grouping â€” call it MonthDue.

â¸»

Step 4 â€“ Group by Risk Event + Month
	1.	Home â†’ Group By
	â€¢	Group by: Risk Event ID, MonthDue
	â€¢	Operation: â€œAll Rowsâ€ (not Sum yet).
	2.	In the grouped table column, weâ€™ll now calculate counts:
	â€¢	Click the small table icon in one group.
	â€¢	Add a custom column:

